This paper deals with natural language understanding and entity linking in tweets, which falls under the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper proposes a new approach for implicit entity linking in tweets, which is a problem related to natural language understanding and information retrieval. The paper also discusses the importance of exploiting contextual knowledge associated with an entity, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence and machine learning. Finally, the paper deals with data analysis and modeling, which are relevant to social and information networks.
